channel.title: Deobfuscated new engine client
channel.description: As of yet I haven't thought of a good solution to the random variable swapping and such, but I have managed to hack saevion's opaque predicate remover into functionality (take that, folks who had a fit in RegeX's thread). This source *will* compile, and that's the most important thing at the moment. I'm only releasing this to the community members for now, because in all likelyhood the first few people to try a java bot will get their asses banned instantly and I don't want a horde of angry noobs after me.

item.title: Deobfuscated new engine client
item.dc:creator: @Teh_Freak Teh Freak
item.description:
@Teh_Freak wrote:

Krichevskoy:
Cheater @ sythe.org:

http://rsclient.nickstallman.net/Main_Page

Thanks Mopar for the deobbed copy btw.

I'll assume he means the board in general so I'll address it as such.
Dearest "trusted" community members:
If I wanted it spread, I would have posted it in a public board.
If I post my new ControlFinder, does that get distributed instantly as well? What if I want to seize this opportunity to keep cheats out of the hands of the abusers? The people who don't know anything about what they're actually doing and can only handle a cheat if it takes less than 30 seconds to work perfectly, and then bitch that they can't do anything else with their computers while running 20 bot instances? Maybe only for a little while to let the developers figure out what's happening before noobs go off drawing attention to us by getting their entire mining team banned instantly through the sheer stupidity of having ten identical characters doing the same thing at the same time?

Once cheating reaches a certain point, it almost takes Jagex rebuilding their entire game to stop us (RSC -> RS2;RS2 weekly updates;RS2.A engine -> RS2.B Engine). Every time they upgrade cheating gains an extra magnitude of difficulty. In the meantime, the game becomes almost impossible to play OR cheat at because of all the idiots clogging the servers. LET'S MAKE A DECENT CHEAT BEFORE WE GO FUCKING THINGS UP AGAIN PLEASE.

Couldnt agree with you more, and many thanks for the release, started on comparison of classes, and methods, generally, from what i can tell, most MAIN methods, have hardly no changed, so its kind of easy to find the old names for the methods, but its just hard to find where they're placed, but yea, many thanks.

Read full topic
